<headline>Severe Weather Statement issued July 04 at 12:22AM CDT until July 04 at 3:00AM CDT by NWS Bismarck</headline>
<description>...A SEVERE THUNDERSTORM WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 1145 PM MDT
FOR EASTERN BOWMAN...HETTINGER...EASTERN SLOPE...SOUTHERN STARK AND
WESTERN ADAMS COUNTIES...
At 1121 PM MDT, severe thunderstorms were located along a line
extending from 8 miles south of Dickinson to 12 miles northeast of
Reeder to 10 miles north of Ralph, moving east at 40 mph.
HAZARD...70 mph wind gusts and penny size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Expect considerable tree damage. Damage is likely to mobile
homes, roofs, and outbuildings.
Locations impacted include...
Hettinger, Mott, New England, Scranton, Reeder, Regent, Bucyrus,
Havelock, Gascoyne, Bowman Haley Dam, Buffalo Springs, Lefor and
Schefield.
THUNDERSTORM DAMAGE THREAT...CONSIDERABLE
HAIL THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.75 IN
WIND THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX WIND GUST...70 MPH</description>
<instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
